            <!-- MISTAKE #4 -->
            <article class="mistake-item animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="mistake-header">
                    <div class="mistake-number">4</div>
                    <h2 class="mistake-title">Not Qualifying Leads Before Sending Techs</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="mistake-content">
                    <p>How many times has your tech driven 45 minutes to a "job" only to discover the customer wanted a free estimate, was just price shopping, or isn't even home? <strong>Unqualified leads waste your most expensive resource: technician time.</strong></p>

                    <p>Every wasted truck roll costs you $150-$300 in labor, fuel, and opportunity cost. Multiply that by 10-20 bad dispatches per month, and you're burning $3,000+ on leads that should have been filtered out in the first conversation.</p>

                    <div class="cost-badge">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"></path></svg>
                        Cost: $2,000 - $6,000/month in wasted truck rolls
                    </div>

                    <div class="fix-box">
                        <div class="fix-box-header">
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"></path><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"></polyline></svg>
                            <span>The Fix</span>
                        </div>
                        <p>Implement intelligent qualification in your lead response that asks the right questions upfront—job scope, timeline, budget expectations—so only ready-to-book customers make it onto your calendar.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>

            <!-- MISTAKE #5 -->
            <article class="mistake-item animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="mistake-header">
                    <div class="mistake-number">5</div>
                    <h2 class="mistake-title">Letting Price Shoppers Slip Away Without a Fight</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="mistake-content">
                    <p>"I'm getting a few quotes" is not a dead end—it's an opportunity. But most home service companies treat price shoppers like lost causes, giving them a number and hoping for the best.</p>

                    <p><strong>Price shoppers convert at 15-25% when you have proper objection handling in place.</strong> That means if you're getting 20 price shoppers a month, you could be booking 3-5 additional jobs just by having better conversations.</p>

                    <p>The key is communicating value, addressing concerns, and staying engaged—not just throwing out a price and crossing your fingers.</p>

                    <div class="cost-badge">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"></path></svg>
                        Cost: $3,000 - $7,500/month in winnable deals
                    </div>

                    <div class="fix-box">
                        <div class="fix-box-header">
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"></path><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"></polyline></svg>
                            <span>The Fix</span>
                        </div>
                        <p>Deploy proven objection-handling scripts that communicate value and address "I need to think about it" concerns. AI systems can do this automatically, keeping leads warm until they're ready to book.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>

