            <!-- MISTAKE #6 -->
            <article class="mistake-item animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="mistake-header">
                    <div class="mistake-number">6</div>
                    <h2 class="mistake-title">Using the Wrong Communication Channels</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="mistake-content">
                    <p><strong>Phone calls have a 15% answer rate. Texts have a 98% open rate.</strong> Yet most home service companies still rely primarily on calling leads back—and then wonder why half their callbacks go to voicemail.</p>

                    <p>Modern homeowners (especially under 45) prefer text communication. They're in meetings, at kids' soccer games, or simply screening unknown numbers. Calling them repeatedly doesn't make you persistent—it makes you annoying.</p>

                    <div class="stat-callout">
                        <div class="stat-callout-value">98%</div>
                        <p class="stat-callout-text">of text messages are opened (vs. 15% phone answer rate)</p>
                        <p class="stat-callout-source">Source: Gartner Communications Study</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="cost-badge">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2v20M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 0 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 0 7H6"></path></svg>
                        Cost: $1,500 - $4,000/month in unreachable leads
                    </div>

                    <div class="fix-box">
                        <div class="fix-box-header">
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"></path><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"></polyline></svg>
                            <span>The Fix</span>
                        </div>
                        <p>Meet customers where they are with omnichannel communication—text, email, chat, and phone—and let them choose their preferred method. AI can manage all channels simultaneously.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>

